---
import Base from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';

const description = "Debt collector response letter — 'This is not my debt.' Tell a debt collector you are not responsible and to stop contacting you unless they can prove otherwise.";
---

<Base title="Debt Collector: Not My Debt Letter — CreditCookbook" description={description} posterTitle="NOT MY DEBT" posterLabel="// debt collector response template">
  <section class="section" data-animate>
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-label" data-animate>// debt collector response — not my debt</span>
      <h2 data-animate style="margin-bottom: 16px;">"This Is Not My Debt"</h2>
      <p data-animate style="max-width: 60ch; margin-bottom: 32px; opacity: 0.7;">Use this letter to tell a debt collector that you are not responsible for the debt they are trying to collect, and that you want them to stop contacting you unless they can provide evidence of your obligation. Stopping contact does not cancel the debt — the collector could still take other action, including suing you or reporting the debt to a credit bureau.</p>

      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 48px;" data-animate>
        <button class="btn btn-primary" onclick="navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('letter').textContent)">Copy letter</button>
        <a href="/recipes/dispute-letters" class="btn btn-ghost">Back to dispute letters</a>
      </div>

      <div id="letter" class="mono-block" style="margin-bottom: 48px;" data-animate>
[YOUR NAME]
[YOUR RETURN ADDRESS]
[DATE]

[DEBT COLLECTOR NAME]
[DEBT COLLECTOR ADDRESS]

Re: [ACCOUNT NUMBER FOR THE DEBT, IF YOU HAVE IT]

Dear debt collector,

I am responding to your contact about collecting a debt.
You contacted me by [PHONE/MAIL], on [DATE] and identified
the debt as [ANY INFORMATION THEY GAVE YOU ABOUT THE DEBT].

I do not have any responsibility for the debt you're trying
to collect.

If you have good reason to believe that I am responsible for
this debt, mail me the documents that make you believe that.
Stop all other communication with me and with this address,
and record that I dispute having any obligation for this debt.
If you stop your collection of this debt, and forward or
return it to another company, please indicate to them that
it is disputed. If you report it to a credit bureau (or have
already done so), also report that the debt is disputed.

Thank you for your cooperation.

Sincerely,

[YOUR NAME]
      </div>

      <div class="card" data-animate>
        <h4 style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Sending instructions</h4>
        <ul style="margin-left: 24px; line-height: 2;">
          <li>Fill in your information on the template and edit as needed to fit your situation</li>
          <li>Print and mail the letter — keep a copy for your records</li>
          <li>Send via certified mail with return receipt for proof of delivery</li>
          <li>Stopping contact does not cancel the debt — you could still be sued</li>
          <li>The collector can still contact you to say they won't contact you again, or to notify you of legal action</li>
          <li>Keep all records of communication</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "HowTo",
    "name": "Debt Collector Not My Debt Letter",
    "description": "Letter to tell a debt collector you are not responsible for the debt and to stop contacting you unless they can prove your obligation.",
    "totalTime": "PT15M",
    "step": [
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Fill in your information", "text": "Complete your name, return address, and the date at the top of the letter."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Add debt collector details", "text": "Fill in the debt collector's name and address, and the account number if you have it."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Record contact details", "text": "Note how the debt collector contacted you (phone or mail), the date, and any information they gave you about the debt."},
      {"@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Print and mail", "text": "Print the letter and mail it via certified mail with return receipt. Keep a copy for your records."}
    ]
  })} />
</Base>
